## Set up MDX in Next.js

### 1. Choose your approach
- **`next-mdx-remote/rsc`** (recommended): Best for App Router with Server Components. MDX can live in your repo or a CMS.
- **`@next/mdx`**: Treats `.mdx` files as pages directly. Simpler but less flexible for dynamic routes.
- This guide uses `next-mdx-remote/rsc` — the standard for App Router projects.

### 2. Install dependencies
  ```
  npm install next-mdx-remote gray-matter
  npm install rehype-highlight rehype-slug remark-gfm
  ```
- `gray-matter`: Parses YAML frontmatter from `.mdx` files.
- `rehype-highlight`: Syntax highlighting for code blocks.
- `rehype-slug`: Adds `id` attributes to headings for anchor links.
- `remark-gfm`: GitHub Flavored Markdown (tables, strikethrough, task lists).

### 3. Create the content directory
- Create `content/blog/` at the project root.
- Add your first post as `content/blog/hello-world.mdx`:
  ```mdx
  ---
  title: Hello World
  date: 2026-06-11
  description: My first blog post.
  author: Your Name
  tags: [intro, nextjs]
  published: true
  ---

  # Hello World

  Welcome to my blog. This is written in **MDX**.

  <Callout>MDX lets you use React components inside Markdown!</Callout>
  ```

### 4. Create MDX utilities (`lib/mdx.ts`)
  ```ts
  import fs from 'fs';
  import path from 'path';
  import matter from 'gray-matter';

  const CONTENT_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'content/blog');

  export interface PostMeta {
    slug: string;
    title: string;
    date: string;
    description: string;
    author: string;
    tags: string[];
    published: boolean;
  }

  export function getAllPosts(): PostMeta[] {
    const files = fs.readdirSync(CONTENT_DIR);
    return files
      .filter(f => f.endsWith('.mdx'))
      .map(filename => {
        const slug = filename.replace('.mdx', '');
        const raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(CONTENT_DIR, filename), 'utf8');
        const { data } = matter(raw);
        return { slug, ...(data as Omit<PostMeta, 'slug'>) };
      })
      .filter(p => p.published)
      .sort((a, b) => new Date(b.date).getTime() - new Date(a.date).getTime());
  }

  export function getPostBySlug(slug: string): { meta: PostMeta; content: string } {
    const filePath = path.join(CONTENT_DIR, `${slug}.mdx`);
    if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {
      throw new Error(`Post not found: ${slug}`);
    }
    const raw = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');
    const { data, content } = matter(raw);
    return { meta: { slug, ...(data as Omit<PostMeta, 'slug'>) }, content };
  }
  ```

### 5. Create custom MDX components (`components/mdx-components.tsx`)
  ```tsx
  import type { MDXComponents } from 'mdx/types';

  export function getMDXComponents(overrides?: MDXComponents): MDXComponents {
    return {
      h2: ({ children }) => (
        <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">{children}</h2>
      ),
      a: ({ href, children }) => (
        <a
          href={href}
          className="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
          target={href?.startsWith('http') ? '_blank' : undefined}
          rel={href?.startsWith('http') ? 'noopener noreferrer' : undefined}
        >
          {children}
        </a>
      ),
      // Custom components available in .mdx files
      Callout: ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (
        <div className="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 my-4 rounded-r-lg">
          {children}
        </div>
      ),
      ...overrides,
    };
  }
  ```

### 6. Blog index page (`app/blog/page.tsx`)
  ```tsx
  import Link from 'next/link';
  import { getAllPosts } from '@/lib/mdx';

  export default function BlogPage() {
    const posts = getAllPosts();
    return (
      <main className="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Blog</h1>
        <ul className="space-y-6">
          {posts.map(post => (
            <li key={post.slug}>
              <Link href={`/blog/${post.slug}`} className="group">
                <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold group-hover:underline">
                  {post.title}
                </h2>
                <p className="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-1">
                  {post.date} &middot; {post.author}
                </p>
                <p className="text-gray-700 mt-2">{post.description}</p>
              </Link>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </main>
    );
  }
  ```

### 7. Blog post page (`app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`)
  ```tsx
  import { notFound } from 'next/navigation';
  import { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote/rsc';
  import remarkGfm from 'remark-gfm';
  import rehypeHighlight from 'rehype-highlight';
  import rehypeSlug from 'rehype-slug';
  import { getAllPosts, getPostBySlug } from '@/lib/mdx';
  import { getMDXComponents } from '@/components/mdx-components';
  import type { Metadata } from 'next';

  interface Props {
    params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
  }

  export async function generateStaticParams() {
    return getAllPosts().map(post => ({ slug: post.slug }));
  }

  export async function generateMetadata({ params }: Props): Promise<Metadata> {
    const { slug } = await params;
    try {
      const { meta } = getPostBySlug(slug);
      return { title: meta.title, description: meta.description };
    } catch {
      return {};
    }
  }

  export default async function BlogPostPage({ params }: Props) {
    const { slug } = await params;
    let post;
    try {
      post = getPostBySlug(slug);
    } catch {
      notFound();
    }
    return (
      <article className="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-16 px-4 prose prose-gray">
        <h1>{post.meta.title}</h1>
        <p className="text-gray-500">{post.meta.date} &middot; {post.meta.author}</p>
        <MDXRemote
          source={post.content}
          components={getMDXComponents()}
          options={{
            mdxOptions: {
              remarkPlugins: [remarkGfm],
              rehypePlugins: [rehypeHighlight, rehypeSlug],
            },
          }}
        />
      </article>
    );
  }
  ```

### 8. Add syntax highlighting CSS
- Import a highlight.js theme in `app/layout.tsx`:
  ```ts
  import 'highlight.js/styles/github-dark.css';
  ```

### 9. Add Tailwind Typography (recommended)
  ```
  npm install @tailwindcss/typography
  ```
- Add to `tailwind.config.ts`:
  ```ts
  plugins: [require('@tailwindcss/typography')]
  ```
- Apply the `prose prose-gray` classes on the article wrapper for automatic content styling.

### Common Errors & Fixes
- **`Cannot find module 'gray-matter'`** → Run `npm install gray-matter`. It is not bundled with next-mdx-remote.
- **`ENOENT: no such file`** → `getPostBySlug` can't find the MDX file. The slug must exactly match the filename (without `.mdx`). Call `notFound()` to handle missing slugs gracefully.
- **`You're importing a component that needs next-mdx-remote/rsc`** → Remove `'use client'` from the page component. `MDXRemote` from `/rsc` is Server-Component-only.
- **MDX custom components not rendering** → The component name in MDX (e.g., `<Callout>`) must exactly match the key in your components map — it is case-sensitive.
- **Frontmatter not parsed** → Ensure the YAML block starts at the very first line, delimited by `---`. No blank lines or content before the opening `---`.
- **Syntax highlighting has no color** → A `highlight.js` CSS file must be imported. The HTML has the classes but no styles without it.
- **`params` type error in Next.js 15** → `params` is a `Promise` in Next.js 15. Use `const { slug } = await params;`.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT use `MDXRemote` from `next-mdx-remote/rsc` in a Client Component. For client-side MDX rendering use `next-mdx-remote` (the non-RSC import).
- Do NOT read MDX files from the `public/` directory. Use a `content/` directory at the project root and read with Node `fs`.
- Do NOT render untrusted user-generated content through MDX — MDX can execute arbitrary JavaScript.
- Do NOT use `@next/mdx` for a blog with dynamic `[slug]` routes. It is designed for static `.mdx` page files, not a directory of posts.
- Do NOT skip `generateStaticParams` for a blog. Without it, every page is server-rendered on first request, which is slow and misses static optimization.
- Do NOT bundle `gray-matter` into client components. Frontmatter parsing is server-only work.
